KAIZER Chiefs defender Eric “Tower” Mathoho cherishes every single moment he spends with his family. Mathoho posted a picture with his brother and mother on Twitter, revealing that she is his only pillar of strength in the whole world.  The tough as teak player was very close with his late sister Balanganani who passed away in July last year. The 31-year-old also enjoys spending some quality time with his son whenever he is free from club duties. Tower also likes riding a bicycle during his spare time.  